en_755370_0	The Planting of Kap tradition for the historic Esala Perahera Festival took place at the auspicious time today at the four Maha Devales The Kap planting tradition took place at the Natha, Vishnu, Pattini and Kataragama Devales.
en_755370_1	This is the first tradition of the Esala Maha Perahera Festival.
en_755370_2	The receipt of rain at the proper time as well as prosperity is expected through the tradition.
en_755370_3	Another aim of participating in the Perahera is to secure blessings for security and welfare.
en_755370_4	The Basnayake Nilames and the Chiefs of the Devales were among the group that joined in the occasion.
